article.headline: Utah Valley St. 88, Texas-Pan American 84
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- Isiah Williams scored 33 points Thursday and Utah Valley beat Texas-Pan American 88-84. Holton Hunsaker had 14 points, Ben Aird scored 12 and Justin Baker had 10 points and seven rebounds for the Wolverines (13-9, 5-1 Great West), who raced to a 50-28 halftime lead and finished the game with 55 percent shooting from the field. Aaron Urbanus scored 23 points to lead the Broncs (3-20, 0-7), who were playing their first home game since Dec. 29. Brandon Provost scored 21 and Ruben Cabrera had 15 points. Texas-Pan American has lost 14 straight, with its last win coming over Victory University on Dec. 5.
